title: Grateful Dead Live at Veterans Memorial Coliseum on 1977-05-05
description:
Set I
Promised Land
Sugaree
Mama Tried >
El Paso
Tennessee Jed
Looks Like Rain
Deal
Lazy Lightning >
Supplication
Peggy-O
The Music Never Stopped
Set II
Bertha
Estimated Prophet
Scarlet Begonias >
Fire On The Mountain >
Good Lovin'
Saint Stephen >
Sugar Magnolia

Encore:
Johnny B. Goode
 
Comment
Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Keith Godchaux - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums
Donna Jean Godchaux - Vocals

reviews.review_text: to the below reviewer.. I clean up a lot of gaps, dead air, dropouts, etc by using Audacity to edit the tracks I wish to. I'll also apply fade in's and fade outs as needed.

Not Me! Due to previous misinterpretations, I'm updating this review.

Excellent show.  Excellent mix.

That is all.

Beauty This show is outstanding! Love the Sugaree to really set the tone. Like most of Eternal Spring ‘77. Not much filler here. Peggy O also lovely & a banging Supplication jam. I prefer this Scarlet/Fire to Cornell. Keeping in mind there is absolutely no such as the best version of any song ever, just individual’s personal favourites. Which is as it should be. Stephen is also a corker. No Jerry ballad (Wharf, Dew etc) in 2nd set, but still a great show leading into the real meat of Spring ‘77 (Cornell, Buffalo et all). Great stuff
